CHANGES0007 - Recursive punchIn + simplicial identity

Major changes:
1. Changed punchIn from <ᵇ-based with-clause to recursive definition:
   - punchIn (zero , _) j = fsuc j
   - punchIn (suc a , p) (zero , _) = fzero
   - punchIn (suc a , p) (suc c , q) = fsuc (punchIn (a , p) (c , q))
   - Key property: punchIn (suc a) (suc c) = suc (punchIn a c) definitionally
   - All existing proofs still compile with new definition

2. Added punchIn-ℕ (ℕ → ℕ → ℕ) mirroring Fin punchIn

3. PROVED simplicial-ℕ: punchIn-ℕ a (punchIn-ℕ b c) ≡ punchIn-ℕ (suc b) (punchIn-ℕ a c)
   when a ≤ b. 4-line proof by pattern matching:
   - zero case: refl (definitional!)
   - suc/zero case: ⊥ from hypothesis
   - suc/suc/zero case: refl
   - suc/suc/suc case: cong suc (IH)

4. PROVED punchIn-fst: fst (punchIn i j) ≡ punchIn-ℕ (fst i) (fst j)

5. PROVED simplicial (Fin level): punchIn i (punchIn j k) ≡ punchIn (fsuc j) (punchIn i' k)
   when fst i ≡ fst i' and fst i ≤ fst j. By pattern matching + cong fsuc + IH.

6. Added imports: snotz, znots, injSuc from Cubical.Data.Nat

Remaining holes: d-preserves-alt (2 holes)
Remaining postulates: d² (general), cπ-homotopic-to-id, contractible-with-section

757 lines (up from 702). Growth from simplicial identity infrastructure. No useful work lost.
